name: Yummy Artichoke Dip
author: CYEPP
summary: Mmmmm Mmmm good!!! Generous amounts of Parmesan cheese make this dip a sure crowd pleaser. Serve with corn chips. Substitute chopped jalapeno peppers for the green chiles if you dare.
ingredients: 1 (6.5 ounce) jar marinated artichoke hearts, drained and quartered
1 (4 ounce) can chopped green chile peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
In a medium bowl, mix the artichoke hearts, mayonnaise, 1 cup Parmesan, cream cheese and green chile peppers
Scoop the mixture into a pie pan or medium baking pan
Top with the remaining 1/2 cup of Parmesan
Bake for 25 minutes or until bubbly and slightly browned
